{
  "stem": "13063.4",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So one, two, or three postcards like this came back, and immediately there was hope, and-- and everybody was talking.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was a postcard here and a postcard there, to this and that family, and the people who were transported out are OK.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But this was a German scheme, of course, to keep the lid-- to keep the lid over the-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] of the Jews, that they should still maintain some hope of-- for those who were transported away.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But of course, these were-- they were all put to death without an exception.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] This started in 1941 and continued 1942.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The mood became blacker and blacker all the time, because, after all, peoples did not know-- did not know what-- what's-- what was happening.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They did not know about the Wannsee Conference in German, that-- that the Final Solution was-- was decided upon-- the Final Solution.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They didn't know about it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Nobody knew about it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "This was a tightly kept secret by the Germans.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, all the time, my-- my family, members of my family, my-- on my mother's side, of course.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They're all the time were taking away, for-- with every transport.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Nobody knew in advance.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were-- there were rumors that tomorrow or-- or the day after or in-- in three days, there is going to be a-- a transport again.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were rumors, unconfirmed.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But those rumors were always right.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] When we speak about 1942, October 1942, my mother and my sister-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] as a matter-- we all went with the transports.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "This was-- this was one of the biggest round-ups of the people of the ghetto, in October 20-- October 22, 1942.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
